The Chicago Bears beat the Minnesota
Vikings 40-14 to clinch a playoff berth in the first outdoor
National Football League game in Minnesota in 29 years.   Jay Cutler threw three touchdown passes for the Bears and
Devin Hester set an NFL record with his 14th career kick return
for a score. Chicago improved to 10-4 and captured the National
Football Conferenceâ€™s North Division title.   Brett Favre started at quarterback for the Vikings before
getting knocked out of the game in the second quarter with a
head injury. Minnesota fell to 5-9.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
